para_trans: On recognition of separate title of accounts for SC category under Mukhyamantri Yuva Karyakarta Yojana.
Department of Skills, Employment, Entrepreneurship and Innovation
Government Decision No.: KOUVYU-2024 / Q. No. 187-1 PRACTICE-2
Madam Cama Marg, Martyrdom Rajguru Chowk,
Reference: - Government Decision No. -Synchronous-2024 / Q.No. 90 / Vyathi-3, D. 09.07.2024.

Introduction: - To enhance the employability of the youth of the state by providing them hands-on training after their education. The "Mukhyamantri Yuva Karyakarta Shiksha Yojana" has been implemented under the government decision of 09.07.2024. The financial coverage of the Mukhyamantri Yuva Karyakarta Yojana is extensive. Suggestions were received from the Finance Department that separate headings for general / SC / ST should be proposed under the scheme so that the expenditure thereon can be managed sector wise.

Accordingly, the proposal submitted for getting a separate title of account for the SC category under the Chief Minister's Youth Work Training Scheme was approved by the Finance Department as well as the Ministry of Finance. The Accountant General (Accounts and Licensure) has agreed. Accordingly, the government was considering approving a separate accounting title for the Scheduled Caste category under the Chief Minister's Youth Work Training Scheme.
Government Decision: Under the Chief Minister's Youth Affairs Training Scheme, the following separate headings are being approved for the SC category: -

Special Component Plan for Schedule Caste
